SIMPLE SHELL (2) "20 December 2023" "Holberton School" "C - Simple Shell"

NAME
hsh - simple command line interpreter

SYNOPSIS
hsh [FILENAME]

DESCRIPTION
Simple command line interpeter that reads commands from a file or from the
standard input and executes them.

INVOCATION
hsh can be invoked interactively and non-interactively.

if hsh is invoked with standard input, it reads and executes received commands in order.

if command line arguments are supplied upon invocation, hsh treats the first argument
as a file to read from and execute commands.
Supplied file should contain 1 command per line.

SEE ALSO
sh(1)

AUTHOR
Augusto Chi and Alfredo Lehman
